olitical, social, and economic life in a renewed America. Speth envisions a future that will be well worth fighting for. In short, this is a book about the American future and the strong possibility that we yet have it in ourselves to use our freedom and our democracy in powerful ways to create something fine, a reborn America, for our children and grandchildren.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aEnvironmental policyxUnited States. 0aEnvironmental policyzUnited States 0aEnvironmental policyzUnited States. 0aProgressivism (United States politics) 0aProgressivism (United States politics). 0aSocial justicexUnited States. 0aSocial justicezUnited States 0aSocial justicezUnited States. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Economic Policy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300184686423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300184686.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles